Again, you wantabe human beings can not Leave me alone. Kindly note this site was started by a fellow war protestor, Marc Weiss, for the purpose of interaction between the sides, not for, as Ed says being &quot;allowed to talk to combat veterans&quot;. What egotistical crap Ed.  <br><br>
This site should actually be called the Rat Pack Hyena Sign up list. It reads like it is, a non thinking bunch of macho combat caveman who have grossed out most of the real intellects of this site with the Native American Mumbo Jumbo, the Helicopter lingo, and the blantent racism and sexism.  It racism and sexist, and John Wayne Macho-ism is for you, then this is your thread.<br><br>
But Ed, who started this attact on me again, (1) why do I &quot;bring out the worse in you&quot; as &quot;mom&quot; says?  Could it be the truth? Could it be reality?  Could it be that the measure of your intensity and hatred of me exactly mirrors the emptiness of your lives?<br><br>
Ed, you say I am not a Doctor-Prove it or shut up. I have a Ph.D. hanging in my office, but I guess you know better. You call me a draft dodger (which is equal to someone calling you a baby killer by the way) after I have dozens of times said I was not. I was a legal C.O. who did his two years of Alternative Service per Federal Law. That is a far cry from running to Canada (which I was against). I have never called you a baby killer, so why do you insult me with &quot;draft dodger&quot;?  That is typical of your failure to think.<br>
You call me a drug addict. Really, again, where is your proof or is throwning slurs the best you can do.  Anti God, too? Gee, where did you get that one?  Whats next Ed, will you call me a pedophile or nechrophiliaic next? (go look em up ed).<br><br>
If others want to understand the Viet Nam War, and the division it caused in the USA, then they must hear both sides, actually all three sides. One is the unrepenten combat and proud side your pack represents, the worse being the bloodthirsty macho cave man cook. The second group is the active war resistors, and related groups. The third, are the other veterans who don't need to play &quot;army&quot; anymore, and have grown up and beyond their need to continually pat themselves on the back and keep telling themselves they were ok.<br><br>
What is it about you guys that can not seperate fact from personal attack?  It was a stupid political war that never should have been faught. PERIOD. That does NOT mean that there was not many, many acts of personal courage in warfare.  But, for all the acts of personal courage, of which you all should be proud, you were wrong to be their, and you, due to the politics of your leadership, lost the war.  58,000 Americans and a few million Asians died for nothing. That is the fact. The Commies won anyway.<br><br>
If I had risked my life like most of you did, I would be made as hell at the government that set me up. I could also admit to myself that I could have NOT GONE. Having gone, you can come to terms with that decision and subsequent betrayal, and grow up and over it.  <br><br>
Why must you constantly attack the messenger, when it is the king you hate?  You follow cook like sheep, just like you followed the recruiting posters or the draft board, and ended up in the Jungle. If you had openned your minds then, or even now, you might wake up and learn. But Nooooo,<br>
you must launch constant and erronous attacks at me, because I keep reminding you that the real blame is yours, my friends, all yours.  <br><br>
Thousands of Americans refused to get drafted, Thousands of Americans said HELL NO, WE WON'T GO, and these Thousands of Americans are the real patriots, the real unsung heros, who also risked their lives in some cases, got no benefits, nor recognition, but more importantly, have forgiven you for being combat veterans of the &quot;war&quot; in Viet Nam.<br><br>
The truth stings doesn't it?  Keep attacking me if you must, if you are to afraid to face reality and truth.  I was right in the 60's, right in the 70's, and guess what, I still am right, only now history has finally caught up with my opinion and &quot;we&quot; are the majority in America.  Is being the pround combat veteran minority so painful, that you must constantly beat the drum?  Looks like it.  Ignore me, I hope, but you won't. Because  underneath all of this, esp. Cook and Ed, you are keyboard cowards who can't argue truth, logic, and fact.  <br><br>
Face me on line, or b/c, anytime, anywhere, one to one. I don't need a pack mentality to keep telling me &quot;attaboy&quot; or call insults or slurs.  You tell me, what is the sense, and what is there to be proud of, in surviving a war, other than you got out alive?  
